I came to San Francisco for food. So, of course I had to stop by Brenda's. I've seen these crawfish beignets allll over social media and had to try. I ubered here and most people told me to be careful and try not to fear for my life. It was in a shady neighborhood but I would come here all over again because the food was just that good. I got the beignet for takeout and ate it at the airport. I had so many regrets as I took my first bite. Regret that I only got one order. Regret that I didn't order other items on the menu. Regret that I didn't order different types. It was slightly cold when I ate it......and I still thought it was the best thing since sliced bread. Imagine if I had it at the restaurant warm? I don't think my mouth/brain/body can fathom it. Will be back soon Brenda's! You warm my soul!

Took the cable car and walked 10 mins to this place. Totally worth it! Must-try: crawfish beignet, fried chicken and shrimp and grits!

Let's be real here, the Bay Area really knows absolutely NOTHING about soul food/southern food/creole food, and most people out here are EXTREMELY easy to please and easily impressed by these type of restaurants, so I don't take much stock in their reviews and taste buds. Unless, you're someone from the south (I'm not), then I'll listen. The south has yet to really make its presence known here in the Bay Area. Most places, this one being no exception, have the same basic items (fried chicken, collard greens, yams, shrimp and grits, red beans and rice), and many can't even do those things right. I can have way better soul food in NJ where I'm from! With that said, I avoided this place for SEVERAL years after being greatly disappointed by the food. I decided to give them another shot just to see, although my ordering is admittedly very calculated, and I stick to the basics. I don't order any of the beignets (had those in the past and was very disappointed as they were pretty dry and thick instead of airy and puff pastry and buttery). I also stay away from the shrimp and grits and étouffées, and gumbos as I'm picky about my shrimp and seafood in general, and this is not the south. Instead, I stick with their wings (love the flavor and crispiness), oyster flight (their oysters are soooooo gooooodd, and the cheese grits (cooked well and right amount of cheese) along with a watermelon ice tea (good, but wish it was a little sweeter). Service is also pretty good and staff is really friendly for it to be so busy. Is this place a love...far from from it! But I know what to order and that helps.

Came here 30 minutes before closing. It was packed. But luckily we were able to get seated instantly. Live jazz music was being played by a 3 man band. That was a pleasant surprise and made me feel like I was in new Orleans. I've always wanted to come here as I heard great things about their shrimp and grits. For the table I ordered plain begneits (3) to start. Bigger and thicker than in the French quarter but not far off. A great choice. I ordered the shrimp and grits and asked if they can make it without bacon. The waiter said "sure, we get that request a lot." Yay! I love when places can make accommodations. The grits were very flavorful. The shrimp was ok but blended well with the shrimp. I added a little salt and pepper to taste. Next thing I knew I had eaten the whole bowl lol. The neighborhood is a little shady but you forget that you're in the tenderloin once inside.

Finally I was able to try Brenda yesterday! I don't wanna go by myself because of the neighborhood. We got there in the mid week for breakfast and no waiting line. The ambience is unbelievable and my friend said it's very New Orlean like. I order the Crispy Pork Belly and Sweet Watermelon House Tea (free refill). It was DELISH!!!!!!!! The service is excellent and we chat with our waiter as she is very friendly originally from Hawaii. She tell us the story about Brenda. The whole place is very relaxing and everyone has a smile on their face with their food. Happy people happy food!

I hate the wait for brunch but honestly the food and service are worth it. Their serving sizes are huge and the food is rich. I love their bloody marys and their tasty coffee! The shrimp and grits is one of my favorites! Love the beignets as well.

This place has great food and it's super cute!! The inside is light and fun making this the perfect place for brunch. We went at 12 on a Thursday and there was only a short wait. I got the BTC chicken breast side and it was sooo good. The breading was crunchy and the meat was cooked perfectly. My friend got the eggs Benedict and that looked to die for. I would def recommend getting that if you stop by.

I have only ordered take out from this location. The only reason that they didn't get 5 stars is because of how greasy the chicken was. My friend ordered it in restaurant and it had the same greasiness. The crawfish beignets and the chocolate beignets are simply to die for. There are no words to describe the warm, doughy pillowy goodness. The greens are bomb, the mac and cheese is good, and I heated the chicken 2 days later and it was still juicy. The flavor was great. They season their food to perfection. That biscuit tho, it has to put Martins Momma biscuit to shame, I nuked it in the microwave 3 days later around a wet paper towel and it was like new. Then they have these fresh, berry preserves to go on it, OMG....Martin hasn't tasted nothing yet lol. This a great taste of soul-food in the heart of San Fran. I ordered like 4 days in a row after I had my first taste. Definitely a go to place in the San Francisco area.

I had to try this place to see what all the buzz and long line is about. It was disappointing, the seating is ridiculous. Seating here is so cramped you can almost touch your neighbors elbow. I tried almost half the menu and everything was just average about 6.5-7/10 and wasn't worth the 40 minute wait. The chicken was dry, but had good flavor. Shrimp po boy cooked well, but bland. Gumbo was average, chicken etouffe was average.I was excited to try the overly hyped stuffed beignets with crawfish and was disappointed. The beignets were nothing special and needed more filling. I'd give this place another try if there is a 10 minute wait max.

Brenda's has a special place in R and my heart's because it was the first place I took him where we had to establish our ordering rule: "n+1" dishes (n = number of people eating). We stopped by here on a whim after an onsen day and as usual, the wait was a bit long (~30mins in a Friday afternoon) but always worth it. This time, we ordered the Spicy Pasta Orleans (seafood pasta with a cream sauce), Pecan French Toast, and the Beignet flight. Our total was $52, a little pricey but worth it for the amount of food we got. My favorite was the Spicy Pasta Orleans! R is a sucker for seafood and I love pasta, so this dish was the favorite from our lunch. There was a good amount of seafood (mussels, Crawfish, shrimp), as well as andouille sausage and pasta. Honestly if we had ordered two plates of this, I would have been alright! The French toast was solid and slightly fluffy without being drowned in syrup, which is a plus for me. The Beignets were perfect as always, and after stuffing ourselves, we had to roll home. The service was fast and responsive, efficient at getting us seated and getting our orders.

I got the pulled pork sandwich and my girlfriend got the pasta and asked for it without sausage. The dish they brought out for her had sausage so not good so far. Overall here was good but far too seasoned. My dish came out and the sandwich fell apart as I ate it. It was very salty and way over seasoned. I couldn't finish it as the flavor was overpowering which never happens. The dishes were fare too pricey for the taste. The beignets however were delicious.

Initially, I thought this restaurant was great. I ordered the cream cheese French toast, Mac and cheese, and fried chicken. The fried chicken and Mac and cheese were really good but the French toast had an excessive amount of blueberry compote which made the dish inedible. It was as though they poured the remainder of the compote that was left over from brunch on the top of my dish. I called back to discuss bringing the food back for a refund and overheard the manager say No like it was nothing. She expressed no desire to address the situation and totally disregarded my complaint. Absolutely terrible customer service and no compassion whatsoever. If anyone asks me about this restaurant I would definitely steer them elsewhere. Terrible lady. You always reap what you sow.

I have been here twice. The first time was years ago and they were fantastic. everything was served hot and flavorful.Tonight's service was not so much. So with a 5 * visit and a 2.5 * visit, I rounded up to four Stars. To be honest, I think tonight's subpar meal was because I was there about 50 minutes before closing. Factor in wait time (it was still crowded) and I think the kitchen staff was just ready to close. Before my crawfish Beignets were delicious and succulent, and tonight they were just meh. The filling was thick and cut like cake. The host was especially nice. But I came for the food, and it just didn't measure up. The red beans and rice were underwhelming and under seasoned. I can't say I won't go again. Gotta have a tie breaker, right? I'll definitely order something else, though.

Too pricey but okay. I feel it's always a rip off of the real thing. If you can get to New Orleans you can stop by but without high expectations. Overall it's decent

I went here on recommendation from a friend and was pleasantly surprised! Brenda's has a cute low key kind of vibe and is very cozy. The line can get CRAZY but we got there at a great time because we were seated about 5 minutes after we put our party on the board! You have to have your WHOLE PARTY to be seated, so that might help you get seated faster. We ordered plain beignets, the Eggs Benedict Florentine, Tofu Hash with a creme biscuit, and biscuits and gravy. The Eggs Benedict Florentine had a really delicious sauce on the top and the potatoes were literally the best. The Tofu Hash was surprisingly tasty! We thought it was going to be super spicy because 1) it's a vegan dish and 2) it's soul food but it had just the right amount of flavor kick to have a little heat, but not make you immediately need a drink to cool your mouth down. The Biscuits and Gravy were outstanding! The biscuit was flaky and buttery, the top a great golden brown color, it really just melted in your mouth! The beignets were good, but I wish they were a little fluffier and had more powdered sugar like the Cafe Dumonde. Overall very good food, a little pricey but worth it to treat yourself, the wait can get very long though so get ready to GO for your Sunday Brunch.

    You have to have your WHOLE PARTY to be seated, so that might help you get seated faster.

    We ordered plain beignets, the Eggs Benedict Florentine, Tofu Hash with a creme biscuit, and biscuits and gravy. The Eggs Benedict Florentine had a really delicious sauce on the top and the potatoes were literally the best. The Tofu Hash was surprisingly tasty! We thought it was going to be super spicy because 1) it's a vegan dish and 2) it's soul food but it had just the right amount of flavor kick to have a little heat, but not make you immediately need a drink to cool your mouth down. The Biscuits and Gravy were outstanding! The biscuit was flaky and buttery, the top a great golden brown color, it really just melted in your mouth! The beignets were good, but I wish they were a little fluffier and had more powdered sugar like the Cafe Dumonde.

    Overall very good food, a little pricey but worth it to treat yourself, the wait can get very long though so get ready to GO for your Sunday Brunch.
